Data
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ BalanceOf
в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ when owner and id are queried
в”‚       в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should return stored balance (including zero for untouched ids)
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ Allowance
в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ when owner, spender, and id are queried
в”‚       в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should return stored allowance (including zero)
в””в”Ђв”Ђ IsOperator
    в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when operator has not been set
    в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should return false
    в””в”Ђв”Ђ when operator has been set via setOperator
        в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should return true

Approve
в””в”Ђв”Ђ Approve
    в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when spender is the zero address
    в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should revert with ERC6909InvalidSpender
    в””в”Ђв”Ђ when spender is not the zero address
        в”њв”Ђв”Ђ it should set allowance[owner][spender][id] to amount
        в”њв”Ђв”Ђ it should emit Approval(owner, spender, id, amount)
        в””в”Ђв”Ђ when amount is zero
            в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should update storage and emit Approval

Operator
в””в”Ђв”Ђ SetOperator
    в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when spender is the zero address
    в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should revert with ERC6909InvalidSpender
    в””в”Ђв”Ђ when spender is not the zero address
        в”њв”Ђв”Ђ it should set isOperator[owner][spender] to approved
        в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should emit OperatorSet(owner, spender, approved)

Transfer
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ Transfer
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when receiver is the zero address
в”‚   в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should revert with ERC6909InvalidReceiver
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when balance is less than amount
в”‚   в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should revert with ERC6909InsufficientBalance
в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ when preconditions hold
в”‚       в”њв”Ђв”Ђ it should decrement caller balance and increment receiver balance by amount
в”‚       в”њв”Ђв”Ђ it should emit Transfer(caller, sender, receiver, id, amount) with caller == sender
в”‚       в””в”Ђв”Ђ when amount is zero
в”‚           в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should succeed without reverting
в””в”Ђв”Ђ TransferFrom
    в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when sender is the zero address
    в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should revert with ERC6909InvalidSender
    в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when receiver is the zero address
    в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should revert with ERC6909InvalidReceiver
    в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when msg.sender is neither sender nor approved operator for sender
    в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when per-id allowance is less than amount and not type(uint256).max
    в”‚   в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should revert with ERC6909InsufficientAllowance
    в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ when allowance is type(uint256).max
    в”‚       в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should not decrease allowance
    в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when msg.sender is approved operator for sender
    в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should not require per-id allowance
    в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when msg.sender equals sender
    в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should not require per-id allowance
    в””в”Ђв”Ђ when preconditions hold
        в”њв”Ђв”Ђ it should decrement sender balance and increment receiver balance by amount
        в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when allowance is finite and sufficient
        в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should decrease allowance by amount
        в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should emit Transfer(caller, sender, receiver, id, amount)

Burn
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ Burn
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when balance is less than amount
в”‚   в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should revert with ERC6909InsufficientBalance
в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ when balance is sufficient
в”‚       в”њв”Ђв”Ђ it should decrement caller balance by amount
в”‚       в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should emit Transfer(caller, caller, address(0), id, amount)
в””в”Ђв”Ђ BurnFrom
    в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when from is the zero address
    в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should revert with ERC6909InvalidSender
    в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when caller is not from
    в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when allowance is less than amount and not type(uint256).max
    в”‚   в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should revert with ERC6909InsufficientAllowance
    в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ when allowance is type(uint256).max
    в”‚       в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should not decrease allowance
    в””в”Ђв”Ђ when preconditions hold
        в”њв”Ђв”Ђ it should decrement from balance by amount
        в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when allowance is finite
        в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should decrease allowance by amount
        в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should emit Transfer(caller, from, address(0), id, amount)

Mint (Mod only; privileged entry)
в””в”Ђв”Ђ Mint
    в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when account is the zero address
    в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should revert with ERC6909InvalidReceiver
    в””в”Ђв”Ђ when account is not the zero address
        в”њв”Ђв”Ђ it should increase balanceOf[account][id] by value
        в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should emit Transfer(caller, address(0), account, id, value)

ExportSelectors
в””в”Ђв”Ђ for each ERC6909 facet (Data, Transfer, Approve, Operator, Burn)
    в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should return an abi.encodePacked list of that facet's external function selectors in the expected order
